@iSazonov I don't need to outline repro steps. Just look at how BAD this code is:

https://github.com/PowerShell/PowerShell/blob/79f21b41de0de9b2f68a19ba1fdef0b98f3fb1cb/src/System.Management.Automation/engine/Modules/ModuleCmdletBase.cs#L345-L352

The ONLY way to clear your AnalysisCache is to restart PowerShell.exe - good luck getting rid of bug reports that PowerShell sucks if people cannot reliably build modules in it.  I realize this was done to speed up powershell, but I keep pointing out to Microsoft engineers they are going about improving performance the wrong way.

@jzabroski 
From the doc: "To disable the file cache, set this value to an **invalid** location, for example: `$env:PSModuleAnalysisCachePath = 'nul'`"


It can be even `'foo'`. It doesn't even matter as long as it's not a valid path.
